shadow often goes back. The Fin-Back is not gregarious. He seems a whale-hater, 
as some men are man-haters. Very shy; always going solitary; unexpectedly 
rising to the surface in the remotest and most sullen waters; his straight and 
single lofty jet rising like a tall misanthropic spear upon a barren plain; 
gifted with such wondrous power and velocity in swimming, as to defy all 
